output: Penguins, unfortunately, cannot fly. They are flightless birds belonging to the family Spheniscidae and are adapted for life in cold environments like Antarctica and surrounding areas. Penguins rely on their streamlined bodies, waterproof feathers, and flippers for swimming and diving rather than flying.
